\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator highlights weaknesses in Programme Design in terms of lack of theoretical depth and some subjects very scantily addressed. That is why it has a non-compliance status. Criteria 4 and 5 need improvement. This relates to staffing capacity as well as whether the institution can demonstrate a transition from training mode to teaching in the higher education sense. In terms of programme design\'2C the list of electives is extensive and it does beg the question as to how the institution will manage\'2C should each student select one elective. In the midst of fairly detailed electives\'2C the anomaly module elective is \'3A Grooming ourself for Employment. This is out of kilter as this should not be an assessed course forming part of the HC in Banking. In addition\'2C there is already a 20 credit module for Self-Leadership which is complusory. This does not form part of the formal requirements for this programme and is excellent as an add-on but definitely not as a credit module.\line \line The programme is lacking in several key disciplinary areas including coverage of the legislation that governs the banking sector\'2C basic economics\'2C and accounting\'29. Some of the elective modules appear out of place in a HE qualification\'2C although they may be perfectly aligned to learnership needs \'28for example \'E2\'80\'9CPreparing for employment and advancement\'E2\'80\'9D for 15 credits. \'28Criterion 1\'2C ii\'2C iv\'29.\line \line The assessment strategy and methods proposed\'2C the learnership context in which the programme will be offered\'2C entry requirement of employment and module content appear to belong more appropriately in a programme aligned to the intentions of the QCTO than to those of the HEQF. Some of the modules appear to be out of place in a Higher Certificate in Banking which should \'E2\'80\'9Cprovide students with the basic introductory knowledge\'2C cognitive and conceptual tools \'E2\'80\'A6 in their chosen field of study\'E2\'80\'9D \'28Criterion 1\'2C ii\'2C iv\'2C vi\'29. \line \line The institution does not appear to have made use of existing higher education paradigms and methods to ensure that the model of provision used will address the overall academic requirements of an HE qualification \'28Criterion 5\'2C ii\'29 in balance with the work-based focus usually allied to a more traditional training intervention \'2F learnership.\line \line The evaluator recommended Non Accreditation of the programme\'2C and the Directorate concurs with the recommendation. \cell \pard 

